        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:46AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 646 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cloud Chief, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carnegie, Mountain View, Gotebo, and Cloud Chief.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
